      <bioghist id="aspace_d7f914088f5bfb04f0a705582047d024">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>The Yale Engineering Association, an alumni organization, was founded in 1914 to encourage and recognize excellence and accomplishment in members of the Yale engineering community. In 1971 it expanded to include all the sciences, becoming the Yale Science and Engineering Association (YSEA).</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_3d2d070d81cd9aa57f6da0c67f40adb0">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The material consists of meeting minutes, subject files and correspondence maintained by Hugo Beit (1953E), who served as secretary from 1963 to 2003.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement id="aspace_d2a9ddab0bd40266fcffaed6efd25c2a">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>The materials are arranged chronologically.</p>  
      </arrangement>
  
